555 S. Africans Die in Traffic Accidents Since
JOHANNESBURG , December 27 ( Xinhua ) -- At least 555 people have died in traffic accidents throughout South Africa since December , Godfrey Maluleke , spokesman for the traffic department said Sunday .
A total of 180 drivers , 197 passengers and 178 pedestrians died in 388 fatal road collisions on South African roads , Maluleke said .
The main contributory factors in the acccidents are speed .
Most of the pedestrians who were killed were knocked over by vehicles while they were walking in the middle of the road under the influence of alcohol , traffic police said .
